            <p>Presented by Charles Coleman Sellers and accessioned, 1945.</p>
        </acqinfo>
        <bioghist id="ref3">
            <head>Biographical/Historical note</head>
            <p>The firm of N. and D. Sellers was engaged in wire working industry and in the manufacture of wool cards and paper molds. After the death of David Sellers in 1813 and the retirement of Nathan Sellers 1817, the business was run by Coleman, son of Nathan, and Samuel and James, sons of David Sellers. In 1828 N. and D. Sellers dissolved with the retirement of Coleman Sellers.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <odd id="ref18">
            <head>Administrative Note</head>
            <p>This record is superseded by, and included in, B P31. It was marked “internal only” in Dec., 2010 and is being kept in the case that it is needed for future administrative needs.</p>
        </odd>
        <odd id="ref19">
            <head>Early American History Not</head>
            <p>This bound volume is part of the Sellers Family Collection. It contains the accounts, receipts, and correspondence for Nathan and David Sellers’ manufacturing firm (N &amp; D Sellers) for the period 1821-1830.</p>
        </odd>
